They are rather poorly preserved. Eighth and ninth tergites not well preserved; ectoprocte (epr sensu
Aspöck et al. 1980
) entire, broader than long; ninth sternite large and appearing terminal ventrally, but with no posterior processes; a pair of long movable heavily sclerotized coxopodites (cp sensu
